    <string name="dialog_help_dismiss">Dismiss</string>
    <string name="dialog_help_button_overview">
        Press a steering wheel button to populate the reading label at the top of the dialog.  This
        reading identifies the button press.  You should do this several times to get an idea of the
        reading variance produced due to "bouncing".
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_button_debounce">
        Debounce: Set this to encompass reading variance.  If your MCU has a 12-bit ADC, you may need
        to check the x10 multiplier.
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_button_action">
        Click/Hold Action: This is the action that will be executed when you "click" or "hold" a
        button.  First select an action category, then select the action you want the button
        to execute.
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_dimmer_overview">
        Choose between the following Dimmer Modes:
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_dimmer_mode_none">
        None: Dimmer commands received from the MCU will be ignored.
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_dimmer_mode_toggle_auto">
        Digital - Toggle Autobrightness:  When the dimmer on, Autobrightness will be toggled on.
        When the dimmer is off, Autobrightness will be toggled off and brightness will be returned
        to its previous state.  This is useful for installations where the light sensor is unblocked.
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_dimmer_mode_manual">
        Digital - User Defined:  When the dimmer is on, brightness will be set to a user defined
        value determined by the wizard.  When the dimmer is off, brightness will be returned to its
        previous value.  This is useful for installations where the light sensor is blocked or no
        light sensor is available.
    </string>
    <string name="dialog_help_dimmer_mode_analog">
        Analog Voltage Map:  This functions in a manner similar to "Digital - User Defined", however
        Analog mode maps minimum and maximum dimmer readings to corresponding user defined brightness
        levels.  This allows the device brightness to be variable, depending on the dimmer setting.
    </string>

